#: ../../computers/basic-system-services.rst:113
msgid "Configuration of the LDAP server in use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/basic-system-services.rst:115
msgid ""
"Several LDAP servers can be operated in a UCS domain. The primary one "
"used is specified with the |UCSUCRV| :envvar:`ldap/server/name`, further "
"servers can be specified via the |UCSUCRV| "
":envvar:`ldap/server/addition`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/basic-system-services.rst:119
msgid ""
"Alternatively, the LDAP servers can also be specified via a *LDAP server*"
" policy. The order of the servers determines the order of the computer's "
"requests to the server if a LDAP server cannot be reached."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/basic-system-services.rst:123
msgid ""
"By default only :envvar:`ldap/server/name` is set following the "
"installation or the domain join. If there is more than one LDAP server "
"available, it is advisable to assign at least two LDAP servers using the "
"*LDAP server* policy in order to improve redundancy. In cases of an "
"environment distributed over several locations, preference should be "
"given to LDAP servers from the local network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/basic-system-services.rst:133
msgid "Configuration of the print server in use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/basic-system-services.rst:135
msgid ""
"The print server to be used can be specified with the |UCSUCRV| "
":envvar:`cups/server`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/basic-system-services.rst:138
msgid ""
"Alternatively, the server can also be specified via the *Print server* "
"policy in the UMC module :guilabel:`Computers`."
msgstr ""

