msgid "Logging/retrieval of system messages and system status"
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/basic-system-services.rst:149
msgid "Log files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/basic-system-services.rst:151
msgid ""
"All UCS-specific log files (e.g., for the listener/notifier replication) "
"are stored in the :file:`/var/log/univention/` directory. Services write "
"log messages their own standard log files: for example, Apache to the "
"file :file:`/var/log/apache2/error.log`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/basic-system-services.rst:156
msgid ""
"The log files are managed by :program:`logrotate`. It ensures that log "
"files are named in series in intervals (can be configured in weeks using "
"the |UCSUCRV| :envvar:`log/rotate/weeks`, with the default setting being "
"12) and older log files are then deleted. For example, the current log "
"file for the |UCSUDL| is found in the :file:`listener.log` file; the one "
"for the previous week in :file:`listener.log.1`, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/basic-system-services.rst:163
msgid ""
"Alternatively, log files can also be rotated only once they have reached "
"a certain size. For example, if they are only to be rotated once they "
"reach a size of 50 MB, the |UCSUCRV| :envvar:`logrotate/rotates` can be "
"set to ``size 50M``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/basic-system-services.rst:167
msgid ""
"The |UCSUCRV| :envvar:`logrotate/compress` is used to configure whether "
"the older log files are additionally zipped with :command:`gzip`."
msgstr ""

