#: ../../computers/ucr.rst:6
msgid ""
"|UCSUCR| is the central tool for managing the local system configuration "
"of a UCS-based system. Direct editing of the configuration files is "
"usually not necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/ucr.rst:10
msgid ""
"Settings are specified in a consistent format in a registry mechanism, "
"the so-called *Univention Configuration Registry variables*. These "
"variables are used to generate the configuration files used effectively "
"by the services/programs from the configuration templates (the so-called "
"*Univention Configuration Registry templates*)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/ucr.rst:16
msgid "This procedure offers a range of advantages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/ucr.rst:18
msgid ""
"It is not usually necessary to edit any configuration files manually. "
"This avoids errors arising from invalid syntax of configuration settings "
"or similar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/ucr.rst:22
msgid ""
"There is a uniform interface for editing the settings and the different "
"syntax formats of the configuration files are hidden from the "
"administrator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/ucr.rst:25
msgid ""
"Settings are decoupled from the actual configuration file, i.e., if a "
"software uses a different configuration format in a new version, a new "
"template in a new format is simply delivered instead of performing time-"
"consuming and error-prone conversion of the file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/ucr.rst:30
msgid ""
"The variables used in a configuration file administrated with |UCSUCR| "
"are registered internally. This ensures that when a UCR variable is "
"changed, all the configuration files containing the changed variable are "
"recreated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/ucr.rst:34
msgid ""
"|UCSUCR| variables can be configured in the command line using the "
":command:`univention-config-registry` command (short form: "
":command:`ucr`) or via the UMC module :guilabel:`Univention Configuration"
" Registry`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/ucr.rst:38
msgid ""
"As the majority of packages perform their configuration via |UCSUCR| and "
"the corresponding basic settings need to be set up during the "
"installation, hundreds of |UCSUCR| variables are already set after the "
"installation of a UCS system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../computers/ucr.rst:42
msgid ""
"UCR variables can also be used efficiently in shell scripts for accessing"
" current system settings."
